This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image segmentation. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a novel algorithm for improving reproducibility in automated medical image segmentation. Additionally, the paper involves probabilistic modeling, which could place it in the neural networks and learning (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves statistical modeling, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
